{% extends "base.html.j2" %}

{# Status tab — the "memorable thing" front-door moment per DESIGN.md.
   Server-side rendered from /api/status payload (`s`) so first paint
   carries the quote even before any JS runs (PRD §7.5 progressive
   enhancement).

   #290: status.js polls /api/status every 30s + on visibilitychange,
   patching textContent / [hidden] on data-status-* hooks below so the
   hero reflects what the e-ink is currently showing. Without JS, the
   page is frozen on the first-paint values until manual reload. #}

{% block title %}LitClock — {{ s.time or "Now" }}{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
{# Visually-hidden region heading so screen readers identify the section.
   DESIGN.md a11y: hero is `role="region" aria-labelledby="..."` (lines 287-292). #}
<h2 id="status-heading" class="visually-hidden">Now</h2>

{# Stale-quote banner per locked decision D2. Surface-raised bg, ochre
   --warning border-top. role="status" + aria-live="assertive" — DESIGN.md
   line 296 mandates assertive (not polite) for the stale-quote banner
   first appearance, so the SR interrupts mid-utterance to announce that
   the clock service is paused (polite would defer/skip the announcement).
   Inline Phosphor `clock-countdown` SVG (locked icon-per-action mapping
   line 205); emoji as UI affordance is a DESIGN.md anti-pattern (line 472).

   #290: always render the banner element with [hidden] toggled — status.js
   needs the node to exist so it can show/hide it without DOM creation. #}
<div class="stale-banner" role="status" aria-live="assertive"
     data-status-stale-banner {% if not s.stale %}hidden{% endif %}>
  <svg class="stale-banner-icon" aria-hidden="true" viewBox="0 0 256 256" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor">
    <path d="M128,40a96,96,0,1,0,96,96A96.11,96.11,0,0,0,128,40Zm0,176a80,80,0,1,1,80-80A80.09,80.09,0,0,1,128,216Zm45.66-93.66a8,8,0,0,1,0,11.32l-40,40a8,8,0,0,1-11.32-11.32L156.69,128l-34.35-34.34a8,8,0,0,1,11.32-11.32ZM104,32a8,8,0,0,1,8-8h32a8,8,0,0,1,0,16H112A8,8,0,0,1,104,32Z"/>
  </svg>
  <span class="stale-banner-text" data-status-stale-text>
    {% if s.picked_at_age_s is not none %}
      Clock service may be paused — last quote {{ (s.picked_at_age_s / 60) | round(0, "floor") | int }} min ago
    {% else %}
      Clock service may be paused — no quote published yet
    {% endif %}
  </span>
</div>

{# #274 follow-up #5 — Phase 3 skip banner. Renders when the last
   weekly update.sh run hit a flock timeout on the env.sh merge (rc=75)
   AND the marker is fresh (mtime < 1 day). Self-clears via the reader-
   side staleness clamp; the next clean Phase 3 run also removes the
   marker file. Same banner shape + classes as the stale-banner so the
   DESIGN.md treatment is consistent. #}
<div class="stale-banner" role="status" aria-live="polite"
     data-status-phase3-skip-banner {% if not s.phase3_skipped_at_unix %}hidden{% endif %}>
  <svg class="stale-banner-icon" aria-hidden="true" viewBox="0 0 256 256" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor">
    <path d="M128,24A104,104,0,1,0,232,128,104.12,104.12,0,0,0,128,24Zm0,192a88,88,0,1,1,88-88A88.1,88.1,0,0,1,128,216Zm16-40a8,8,0,0,1-8,8,16,16,0,0,1-16-16V128a8,8,0,0,1,0-16,16,16,0,0,1,16,16v40A8,8,0,0,1,144,176ZM112,84a12,12,0,1,1,12,12A12,12,0,0,1,112,84Z"/>
  </svg>
  <span class="stale-banner-text" data-status-phase3-skip-text>
    Last update skipped the env-vars merge — will retry next Sunday.
  </span>
</div>

{# Hero card per DESIGN.md "Hero card" composition. The paper-grain.svg
   tile is applied via CSS (light mode only) to keep the markup minimal
   and the texture cosmetic. The quote element is `<blockquote>` so
   screen readers announce it as a quote, not a paragraph.

   #290: both branches always rendered with [hidden] toggling, so the JS
   poll can switch between "have quote" and "empty" without creating DOM. #}
<section class="hero" role="region" aria-labelledby="status-heading">
  <div data-status-hero-full {% if not s.quote %}hidden{% endif %}>
    <blockquote class="hero-quote" data-status-quote>{{ s.quote }}</blockquote>
    <p class="hero-attribution">
      {# Format locked in DESIGN.md "Component composition specs":
         "— {Author}, *{Title}*  ·  {HH:MM}". Em-dash, italic title,
         Geist Mono time. The static text in the prefix span — the dash,
         author, and ", " before the title — is rebuilt by status.js as a
         single string so we don't have to mirror Jinja's whitespace rules
         in JS.

         #290 /review fix: the '·&nbsp;' separator stays in the template
         OUTSIDE the [data-status-attr-time] node that JS patches. The
         original markup put '·&nbsp;{time}' inside one node — JS's
         setText() would overwrite textContent to just the time, wiping
         the locked separator after the first poll. Now JS only updates
         the inner bare-time node; the '·&nbsp;' stays in the wrapper. #}
      <span data-status-attr-prefix>— {{ s.author }}{% if s.title %}, {% endif %}</span><span
            data-status-attr-title-wrap {% if not s.title %}hidden{% endif %}><em data-status-attr-title>{{ s.title or "" }}</em></span><span
            data-status-attr-time-wrap {% if not s.time %}hidden{% endif %}> <span class="hero-time">·&nbsp;<span data-status-attr-time>{{ s.time or "" }}</span></span></span>
    </p>
  </div>
  <p class="hero-empty" data-status-hero-empty {% if s.quote %}hidden{% endif %}>
    <em>Starting up…</em>&nbsp; Your first quote should appear within a minute.
  </p>
  {# #309 — graceful disconnect state. Hidden on SSR; status.js reveals
     this when /api/status polling fails (network error, timeout, non-OK)
     and re-hides it on the next successful poll. role="alert" makes
     screen readers announce when it transitions from [hidden] to visible,
     satisfying DESIGN.md line 296 (aria-live="assertive" for errors).
     Headline copy locked by DESIGN.md line 493; help copy approved by
     user 2026-05-28 — non-technical vocabulary (no "IP," "Pi," "address")
     per the gift-recipient persona. #}
  <div class="hero-unreachable" data-status-hero-unreachable role="alert" hidden>
    <p class="hero-unreachable-headline">
      <em>Couldn't reach LitClock.</em>
    </p>
    <p class="hero-unreachable-help">A few things that often help:</p>
    <ul class="hero-unreachable-tips">
      <li>Make sure your clock is plugged in and the screen is lit</li>
      <li>Try scanning the QR code on the clock again</li>
      <li>Check that your phone is on the same WiFi as the clock</li>
    </ul>
    <button type="button" class="hero-unreachable-retry" data-status-retry>
      Tap to retry
    </button>
  </div>
</section>

{# 5-row status list per DESIGN.md "Status row list".
   Each row uses an explicit label-value pair so screen readers can pair
   them via `aria-labelledby`. Geist Mono with tabular numerics on the
   value side for SSID / version / uptime per the spec. #}
<dl class="status-rows" aria-label="System status">
  <div class="status-row">
    <dt>WiFi</dt>
    {# DESIGN.md "Status row list" line 379 locks SSID truncation at
       18 chars. Jinja's `truncate(length, killwords=True, end='…')`
       hard-cuts at the locked column count regardless of viewport
       width — CSS ellipsis alone truncates at flex-allowed pixel
       width, not 18 chars. Adversarial /review on M2 caught this. #}
    <dd class="mono" data-status-wifi>{{ s.wifi_ssid|truncate(18, true, "…") if s.wifi_ssid else "—" }}</dd>
  </div>
  <div class="status-row">
    <dt>Weather</dt>
    <dd data-status-weather>{{ s.weather_city or "—" }}</dd>
  </div>
  <div class="status-row">
    <dt>Version</dt>
    <dd class="mono" data-status-version>{{ s.version or "—" }}</dd>
  </div>
  <div class="status-row">
    <dt>Uptime</dt>
    <dd class="mono" data-status-uptime>{{ s.uptime_human }}</dd>
  </div>
  <div class="status-row">
    <dt>Last update</dt>
    {# #330: render to_version + relative time. The version span is hidden
       (via [hidden]) when last_update_version is null so we still degrade
       to "just relative time" on lkg-sha-absent / fresh-install Pis.
       status.js toggles [hidden] + textContent on poll without rebuilding
       the DOM, keeping the mono SHA styling intact. The comma+space
       separator lives in its own [data-…-sep] span for the same reason. #}
    <dd data-status-last-update>
      <span class="mono" data-status-last-update-version{% if not s.last_update_version %} hidden{% endif %}>{{ s.last_update_version or "" }}</span>
      <span data-status-last-update-sep{% if not s.last_update_version %} hidden{% endif %}>,&nbsp;</span>
      <span data-status-last-update-relative>{{ s.last_update_at_relative }}</span>
    </dd>
  </div>
</dl>

{# #309 (3) — opportunistic mDNS bookmark prompt. status.js probes
   litclock.local on first load; if the phone can resolve it on this
   network, this card unhides as a one-time opt-in to navigate to the
   address-stable URL. Add-to-Home-Screen there gives the user a
   bookmark that survives DHCP churn. Silent if probe fails; dismissal
   persists in localStorage. Positioned BELOW the status rows so it
   never competes with the hero — /review caught the original placement
   between hero and rows as a hierarchy violation. #}
<aside class="mdns-bookmark" data-mdns-bookmark role="region"
       aria-label="More reliable connection available" hidden>
  <p class="mdns-bookmark-headline">A more reliable link is available.</p>
  <p class="mdns-bookmark-body">
    Helps your clock keep working even when WiFi changes.
  </p>
  <div class="mdns-bookmark-actions">
    <button type="button" class="mdns-bookmark-switch" data-mdns-switch>
      Switch
    </button>
    <button type="button" class="mdns-bookmark-dismiss" data-mdns-dismiss>
      Not now
    </button>
  </div>
</aside>
{% endblock %}

{% block extra_body %}
<script src="{{ url_for('static', filename='js/status.js') }}" defer></script>
{% endblock %}
